(108, 1, '2012-10-28 23:00:24', '2012-10-28 23:00:24', '<strong>Progress: In Though/Design Process</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">What it is?</span>\r\n\r\nI''ve found that Arduino hits quite a few walls once a certain point of computational complexity and memory requirement is encountered. Already having a good amount of experience with ST Microelectronics ARM Cortex MCU''s[STM32] (And how convoluted and unintuitive their libraries are), I wanted to create a library that embodied the abstraction and simplicity of Arduino''s libraries for the Atmel AVR. Of course, I don''t have the financial ability to do the physical aspect of this, but figure that It won''t hurt to start writing the C libraries.', 'StrongARM', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '31-revision-4', '', '', '2012-10-28 23:00:24', '2012-10-28 23:00:24', '', 31, 'http://www.oneseventyfour.com/?p=108', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
