(109, 1, '2012-11-02 01:42:10', '2012-11-02 01:42:10', 'What I started as RapidSQL and eventually called ''Partner'' is a PHP web application I had written as a sophomore that parsed a mySQL/SQL Server Schema Creation file and would output Data Objects, as well as a functional CRUD-providing front end if needed. At the time, I had quite a bit to learn about organizational principles, especially non-repetition. Being useful/operational as-is, it does so with code that is monolithic at times and incredibly hard to understand at others. My goal with the continuation of this is to make the changes that would make it maintainable and increasingly robust.\n\nI figure this is excellent practice for a scenario where I take a role re-tooling someone else''s solution. Since the first version was finished, I stashed it away and wanted to wait until any ounce of familiarity with the code diminished and it literally felt like I was diving into foreign code. Probably won''t get to this until mid-2013..\n\n<a title="Current Copy" href="http://www.oneseventyfour.com/oldDvs/dev/rapid">Current Copy</a>', 'RapidSQL (Partner)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '26-autosave', '', '', '2012-11-02 01:42:10', '2012-11-02 01:42:10', '', 26, 'http://www.oneseventyfour.com/?p=109', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
